menu "Slave OTA"

config P3A_SLAVE_OTA_MOCK
    bool "Mock slave OTA (test screen ownership without real OTA)"
    default n
    help
      When enabled, slave_ota_check_and_update runs through all the UX
      paths (UI ownership, input lockout, success countdown, reboot)
      but does NOT call esp_hosted_slave_ota_*. Used to verify the
      screen-owning code without burning real OTA cycles. Disable
      before shipping.

config P3A_SLAVE_OTA_MOCK_DURATION_MS
    int "Total mock duration (ms)"
    depends on P3A_SLAVE_OTA_MOCK
    default 10000
    range 2000 60000
    help
      How long the mock OTA takes to climb from 0% to 100%, in
      milliseconds. Defaults to 10 seconds, similar to a real ~1 MB
      transfer over SDIO. Bump this when manually testing the input
      lockout to give yourself a wider window to press buttons or
      issue commands.

endmenu
